DAMATURU – The National Working Committee (NWC) of the All Progressives Congress (APC) has asked Yobe State Governor, Mai Mala Buni, to serve as the returning officer for the Bayelsa State 2019 governorship primaries. The primary election was originally scheduled for 29th August 2019 but was shifted to 31st August 2019. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network This was announced by Abdullahi Bego, the Director-General, Press Affairs, to the Yobe State Governor, in a press statement made available to Daily Independent in Damaturu on Thursday. According to him, “The appointment of His Excellency, Governor Buni, as returning officer was contained in a letter signed by the National Chairman of the party, Comrade Adams Oshiomhole. “Consequently, His Excellency the governor will travel to Yenagoa, Bayelsa State, on Friday 30th August 2019 in time for the primary election on Saturday. “The Governor will return to office in Damaturu on Monday 2nd September 2019 at the end of his assignment”.